The paper focuses on optimizing I/O for big data analytics, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of arrays and nested-loop forms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS). The optimization techniques and framework developed in the paper may also have applications in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE).
